The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                 NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 Pune, July 19 (PTI): An NRI today drove his car at 60kmph through the city with a traffic constable clinging to the bonnet, and needed police to shoot at his tyres to stop him.           
	The constable had walked up to Kamal Jains car to book him for illegal parking when the Canada-based NRI fled. Four people were injured in the chase.                   
	 Srinagar (PTI): Jammu and Kashmir has banned mobile phones in all government-run educational institutions. The decision was taken to prevent interruption in class, state education minister Peerzada Mohammad Sayeed said.                  
	 Patna (PTI): Patna University has sacked a Reader for delivering a classroom lecture on love and his relationship with his girlfriend, who happened to be one of his students. The university syndicate said Matukanth Chaudhary had brought disrepute to the teacher-student relationship and tarnished the varsitys image.                   
	 New Delhi (PTI): Delhi High Court will give its verdict on an appeal in the BMW hit-and-run case on Monday. Sanjeev Nanda, grandson of former Naval Chief S.M. Nanda, has been sentenced to five years imprisonment for mowing down six persons in 1999. Two other persons have also been convicted.                   
	 Harda (PTI): Two youths were killed after allegedly inhaling some poisonous gas while cleaning a well at a village in Harda, Madhya Pradesh. Omprakash had gone down the well to clean it. When he raised the alarm, his friend went down to help and also died.                   
	 Thiruvananthapuram (PTI): A television actor has been arrested for allegedly trying to snatch a gold necklace from a woman in Thiruvananthapuram. Manikantan was tracked down after the woman, an employee of an IT firm, gave his car number to police.                                                                                                                           
